properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 1:30AM PST until January 13 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow showers will decrease today. Heavy accumulation of
snow over the past day will result in difficult driving conditions
this morning.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Darrington, Index, Skykomish, Stevens Pass,
and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade mountains and valleys of Pierce
and Lewis Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski Area,
Paradise on Mount Rainier, Ashford, Randle, and Packwood.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Expect delays or pass closures this morning. Some roads
in the foothills may be closed to down trees and power lines due
to heavy wet snow in the lower elevations overnight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
